This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the use of neural networks for sparse group selection of input variables. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning algorithms for data analysis. The paper also mentions image recognition, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Furthermore, the use of non-linear neural networks suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions biomarker discovery, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the analysis of biological data.
